ght now</em>.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Indeed, when we look back on this h=
ard-edged, unsentimental period in fashion, Philo=E2=80=99s imprint on just=
 about everyone else will be undeniable. And while $1,200 jeans may feel cr=
iminal to most, people with the means to spend that much aren=E2=80=99t nec=
essarily flinching, because
nothing out there is up to par. A friend of mine who=E2=80=99s a big buyer =
of The Row, which supplanted Philo=E2=80=99s C=C3=A9line as the wardrobe fo=
r a certain crowd after she fled the brand in 2017, is now back to buying m=
ostly PP. The truth is, there=E2=80=99s just no one more talented or in tou=
ch with desire than Philo.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;=
">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Once again, for the th=
ird time in her career, she=E2=80=99s managed to tap into something bigger =
that=E2=80=99s happening
in the culture among women of a certain age. The <strong>Miranda July </str=
