ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">But is the collection selling well <em>enough</em>? We may never know, =
given that it=E2=80=99s a
private company, but there are some clues. At the end of 2024, as required =
in the U.K., the company filed a report on its business activities for <em>=
2023</em>. (The British government requires private companies to disclose f=
inancial information, but they don=E2=80=99t have to do it instantly. Still=
, the disclosure requirement itself would be unfathomable to a private Amer=
ican firm=E2=80=94another reason innovation occurs disproportionately outsi=
de the U.K.) The company elected not to include a profit and loss
statement for 2023, which is permitted for businesses of lilliputian size. =
But they were only active for two months that year anyway. (There <em>is </=
em>a mention of =E2=80=9Caccruals or deferred income=E2=80=9D of =C2=A33 mi=
llion, which <em>could</em> refer to the sales they netted in those two mon=
ths, but it=E2=80=99s impossible to tell.)=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;ma=
rgin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">More t=
elling, however, is how much money they spent. By the end of 2023, the comp=
any had
about =C2=A36 million on hand, down from nearly =C2=A315 million at the end=
 of 2022. That=E2=80=99s understandable, given that their employee count ne=
arly doubled (from 49 to 93) and they had to produce a collection. But =C2=
=A39 million is a ton of cash to burn, even with a minority backer like LVM=
H, which owns between 25 and 50 percent of the business.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">From the beginning, the great Phoebe Philo experiment was
orchestrated=E2=80=94intentionally or <em>not</em>=E2=80=94to come in hot b=
ut burn slowly. The initial 2023 drop, for all its messiness, made people l=
ook=E2=80=A6 even if they didn=E2=80=99t buy right away. But as I=E2=80=99v=
e <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uk=
txclJLZ0dVcWdCa0FiZXlXdF91LVlheW55TT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mvc=
GhvZWJlLXBoaWxvcy1mb3VuZGVyLXN5bmRyb21lLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249TGluZStTaGVldCst=
K1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYyNyUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9TGluZStTaGV=
ldCstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYyNyUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF=
9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2M=
TdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjo5=
OTE2NzV9/c99524716c3124e55e99b44ff814c448e8083585a2e9dfd5bedaff327517eb59" =
style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">documented</a> over the =
past year and a half, operating a startup=E2=80=94even with backing from Eu=
rope=E2=80=99s largest company, and with <strong>Delphine</strong> <strong>=
Arnault</strong> on your board=E2=80=94is not easy,
especially when you haven=E2=80=99t done it before, and particularly when t=
he investors have neither the relevant zero-to-one experience nor financial=
 alignment. (Delphine won=E2=80=99t go hungry if Phoebe Philo Limited doesn=
=E2=80=99t work out.) And, frankly, LVMH is just participating with schmuck=
 insurance. It=E2=80=99s arguably in their interest for this business to fl=
atline, for Philo to get this bug out of her house, and then pay her $10 mi=
llion (or more) to once again design for one of their own brands.</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">I=E2=80=99d surmise that the 2023 cash burn reflected an overcon=
fident, bottom-line-insensitive decision to forego wholesale and own the en=
d-to-end retail experience on the company=E2=80=99s own website. While the =
company subsequently jumped into wholesale as a course correction, the prod=
uct in the stores is lagging behind what=E2=80=99s on the site by as much a=
s two weeks. When I went into Bergdorf Goodman on Thursday to try on the
=E2=80=9CBoyish=E2=80=9D tailored trousers ($1,450), which are already onli=
ne, the next-season delivery wasn=E2=80=99t expected until February 11. (I =
asked a rep for Phoebe Philo whether there was a reason behind this approac=
h, but have yet to hear back.) There=E2=80=99s an argument for going direct=
 <em>first</em>=E2=80=94sales of that product will yield higher margins=E2=
=80=94but at the same time, I couldn=E2=80=99t help but feel disappointed t=
hat the item wasn=E2=80=99t available.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-botto=
m:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">Some strategic mistakes are to be expected. After all, =
Phoebe Philo Limited isn=E2=80=99t merely a startup, it=E2=80=99s also a <e=
m>family business</em>, operated by Philo and her husband, <strong>Max Wigr=
am</strong>, both of whom are still reckoning with a year of significant em=
ployee turnover. The company has yet to hire a replacement for <strong>Patr=
ik</strong> <strong>Sil=C3=A9n</strong>, the managing director (British sem=
antics for C.E.O.) who exited last summer. They have, however, managed
to keep <strong>Chantal</strong> <strong>Warner</strong>, a longtime LVMH h=
uman resources executive, as chief people officer for more than a year. War=
ner worked with Philo at C=C3=A9line for half a decade, and it=E2=80=99s cl=
ear she=E2=80=99s helping them recalibrate after designers, customer servic=
e, and operations folks fled (likely for all the usual reasons at startups:=
 high pressure, lack of transparency, etcetera).</p><p style=3D"margin:0;ma=
rgin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Last
month, one of Warner=E2=80=99s old coworkers, <strong>Bruno</strong> <stron=
g>Sialelli</strong>, became the head of Philo=E2=80=99s ready-to-wear colle=
ction. (His appointment was <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFp=
bF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVcWdCa0FiZXlXdF91LVlheW55TT0iLCJocmVmIjo=
